{
  "texts": [
    "However, the negative environmental impact of AI extends beyond CO 2 emissions.",
    "For example, George et al. [26] investigated AI's water usage and showed that GPT-3 consumed 700,000 liters of water during its training phase alone.",
    "The authors call for urgency to address this concern, as freshwater scarcity is a global problem [27].Tools for monitoring the negative environmental impact of AI.",
    "Another relevant research direction is the development of tools to measure or estimate the negative impacts of LLMs on the environment.",
    "For example, Budennyy et al. [28] introduced Eco2AI, an open-source package to track the energy consumption and CO 2 emissions of AI models."
  ]
}